This can represent an equal contribution of two modal points.

Example Integration:

# Apply Hadamard gates to initialize superpositions
circuit.h(0)  # Apply H to qubit 0
circuit.h(1)  # Apply H to qubit 1
Meaning in MTT:
Superpositions could represent modal uncertainty or overlapping modal states.
Tensor components evolving simultaneously across multiple dimensions.
2. Creating Entanglement
Hadamard gates can pair with controlled gates (e.g., CNOT) to create entangled states, which are useful for modeling dependencies or correlations between tensor components.

