1. Core Definitions

Let:

∣ψ1⟩|\psi_1\rangle∣ψ1​⟩ and ∣ψ2⟩|\psi_2\rangle∣ψ2​⟩: State vectors in Hilbert spaces H1\mathcal{H}_1H1​ and H2\mathcal{H}_2H2​, respectively.

mmm: Modal parameter encoding the transition between potentiality and actuality.

λi(m)\lambda_i(m)λi​(m): Modal coefficients determining the influence of each transformation mode.

Ui(m)U_i(m)Ui​(m), Vi(m)V_i(m)Vi​(m): Unitary operators parameterized by mmm.

H1H_1H1​: Hermitian operator acting on potential states.

H2H_2H2​: Hermitian operator acting on actualized states.

HmtH_{mt}Hmt​: Hermitian modal tensor operator, defined as the transformative operator that links H1H_1H1​ and H2H_2H2​ through the modal parameter mmm.

2. Fundamental Transformative Equation

The transformative action of HmtH_{mt}Hmt​ on a composite state is given by:

Tmt(∣ψ1⟩,m)=∑iλi(m)(Ui(m)∣ψ1⟩)⊗Vi(m)∣ψ2⟩\mathcal{T}_{mt}(|\psi_1\rangle, m) = \sum_{i} \lambda_i(m) \left( U_i(m) |\psi_1\rangle \right) \otimes V_i(m) |\psi_2\rangleTmt​(∣ψ1​⟩,m)=i∑​λi​(m)(Ui​(m)∣ψ1​⟩)⊗Vi​(m)∣ψ2​⟩

Where:

Tmt\mathcal{T}_{mt}Tmt​: Represents the Hermitian modal tensor transformation.

λi(m)\lambda_i(m)λi​(m): Modal weights dynamically controlled by mmm.

Ui(m)U_i(m)Ui​(m): Encodes the potential evolution of ∣ψ1⟩|\psi_1\rangle∣ψ1​⟩.

Vi(m)V_i(m)Vi​(m): Encodes the actualized evolution of ∣ψ2⟩|\psi_2\rangle∣ψ2​⟩.

mmm: Governs the transition from potential states (H1H_1H1​) to actualized states (H2H_2H2​).

3. Postulates of Modal Tensor Theory

Hermitian Modal Tensor Operator:
