Hermitian Modal Tensor Operator

The Hermitian Modal Tensor Operator is defined as:

Hmt=∑iλi(m)(Ui†(m)Ui(m)⊗Vi†(m)Vi(m))H_{mt} = \sum_{i} \lambda_i(m) \left( U_i^\dagger(m) U_i(m) \otimes V_i^\dagger(m) V_i(m) \right)Hmt​=i∑​λi​(m)(Ui†​(m)Ui​(m)⊗Vi†​(m)Vi​(m))

Where:

Hermiticity: Ensured by the construction λi(m)∈R\lambda_i(m) \in \mathbb{R}λi​(m)∈R and the Hermitian property of Ui†UiU_i^\dagger U_iUi†​Ui​ and Vi†ViV_i^\dagger V_iVi†​Vi​.

Tensor Structure: Encodes a composite operation on both potential and actualized states via the tensor product.

Transformative Dynamics

The transformative action of HmtH_{mt}Hmt​ on a state is:

Tmt(∣ψ1⟩,m)=∑iλi(m)(Ui(m)∣ψ1⟩)⊗Vi(m)∣ψ2⟩\mathcal{T}_{mt}(|\psi_1\rangle, m) = \sum_{i} \lambda_i(m) \left( U_i(m) |\psi_1\rangle \right) \otimes V_i(m) |\psi_2\rangleTmt​(∣ψ1​⟩,m)=i∑​λi​(m)(Ui​(m)∣ψ1​⟩)⊗Vi​(m)∣ψ2​⟩

This expresses the evolution of the system as a modal tensor transformation, where:

